# Corporate-on-Demand — .gitignore for public showcase repos
# Use this when publishing a project to a public GitHub repo.
# Keeps department structure + meaningful artifacts, excludes operational noise.

# === Temp scripts (root-level junk) ===
tmp_*.py
update_state_*.py
it-rotate.py
it-scan.py
improve.sh

# === Internal migration notes ===
MIGRATION-LOG.md

# === JSON cycle logs (bulk machine output) ===
logs/*.json
departments/*/logs/*.json
# Keep README.md inside log dirs (explains log format)
!departments/*/logs/README.md

# === Processed inbox items (just noise) ===
departments/*/inbox/done/

# === Hermes internal plans ===
.hermes/

# === Throwaway department scripts ===
departments/uxui/_update_state.py

# === What STAYS (showcase value) ===
# - All SYSTEM.md (how each dept works)
# - CORPORATE.md, DELEGATION.md (governance)
# - Confluence/ (decisions, pivots, upgrades)
# - R&D pipeline (research → pitches → specs)
# - Creative artifacts (game scripts)
# - QA screenshots, test plans, regression reports, bug reports
# - Board minutes (autonomous governance)
# - CEO reviews (inspection cycles)
# - CTO architecture + directives
# - Security advisories, audits, hardening
# - DevOps pipelines (CI/CD work)
# - Infra audits + runbooks
# - PM changelogs, reports, standards
# - UX/UI designs, research, styleguide
# - IT scans + fixes (housekeeping)
# - Analytics reports
# - state.json (shared brain)
# - All app code (backend, frontend, docker-compose)
# - Active inbox items (not done/)
